# Database Architecture

Portal uses PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM for comprehensive business data management.

## Schema Organization

- `drizzle/schema.ts`: Complete database schema with 20+ tables
- `drizzle/relations.ts`: Foreign key relationships and joins
- `drizzle.config.ts`: Drizzle Kit configuration for migrations
- `lib/database.ts`: Database connection and client setup

## Core Tables

### Authentication & Users
- `portal_user`: User accounts with roles (ADMIN, SALES_MANAGER, SALES_ASSISTANT, MANAGER, USER)
- `portal_session`: User sessions for NextAuth.js/Better Auth
- `portal_account`: OAuth provider accounts (Google, GitHub, etc.)
- `portal_verification`: Email verification tokens

### CRM Core
- `portal_contact`: Contact management with rich metadata
- `portal_company`: Company/organization records
- `portal_company_contact`: Many-to-many relationship between companies and contacts
- `portal_team`: Team management and collaboration

### Business Operations
- `portal_user_task`: Task management with kanban workflows
- `portal_calendar_event`: Calendar events and scheduling
- `portal_team_meeting`: Team meeting records
- `portal_resource_content`: Content management system
- `portal_resource_emails`: Email templates and management

### System & Audit
- `portal_audit_log`: Comprehensive audit trail for all operations
- `portal_api_key`: API key management for external integrations
- `portal_team_activity`: Team activity tracking

## Drizzle ORM Patterns

### Query Patterns
```typescript
// Basic CRUD operations
const users = await db.select().from(user).where(eq(user.role, 'ADMIN'));

// Joins and relations
const contactsWithCompany = await db
  .select()
  .from(contact)
  .leftJoin(company, eq(contact.companyId, company.id));

// Prepared statements for performance
const getUserById = db
  .select()
  .from(user)
  .where(eq(user.id, $1))
  .prepare();

// Transactions for data consistency
await db.transaction(async (tx) => {
  await tx.insert(contact).values(newContact);
  await tx.insert(teamActivity).values(activityLog);
});
```

### Schema Definitions
```typescript
// Table with relationships
export const contact = pgTable('portal_contact', {
  id: text().primaryKey().$defaultFn(() => crypto.randomUUID()),
  firstName: text().notNull(),
  lastName: text().notNull(),
  email: text(),
  companyId: text().references(() => company.id),
  assignedTo: text().references(() => user.id),
  createdBy: text().references(() => user.id),
  status: text('status').notNull().default('Lead'),
  priority: text('priority').default('Medium'),
  // ... other fields
});

// Enums and constraints
role: text('role', {
  enum: ['ADMIN', 'SALES_MANAGER', 'SALES_ASSISTANT', 'MANAGER', 'USER'],
}).default('USER')
```

## Data Relationships

### User-Centric Relations
- Users can have multiple contacts assigned
- Users can be members of multiple teams
- Users create tasks and calendar events
- Users have audit trails for all actions

### CRM Relations
- Contacts belong to companies (optional)
- Companies have multiple contacts
- Teams manage groups of contacts/companies
- Activities track interactions across all entities

### Hierarchical Data
- Tasks can have parent-child relationships (subtasks)
- Teams have hierarchical activity tracking
- Audit logs maintain complete change history

## Database Operations Best Practices

### Performance Optimizations
- Use prepared statements for repeated queries
- Implement proper indexing on frequently queried columns
- Use transactions for multi-table operations
- Leverage Drizzle's query builder for complex joins

### Data Integrity
- Foreign key constraints maintain referential integrity
- Use transactions for related operations
- Implement soft deletes where appropriate
- Validate data at both application and database levels

### Audit & Compliance
- All data modifications create audit log entries
- Track user actions with timestamps and context
- Maintain data lineage for compliance requirements
- Implement proper data retention policies

## Migration Strategy

### Drizzle Kit Usage
```bash
# Generate migrations
npx drizzle-kit generate

# Push schema changes
npx drizzle-kit push

# View migrations
npx drizzle-kit up
```

### Schema Evolution
- Use incremental migrations for schema changes
- Maintain backward compatibility during deployments
- Test migrations against production-like data
- Document breaking changes and migration paths

## Connection Management

```typescript
// Database client setup (lib/database.ts)
import { drizzle } from 'drizzle-orm/postgres-js';
import postgres from 'postgres';

const connectionString = env.DATABASE_URL;
const client = postgres(connectionString);
export const database = drizzle(client);
```

## Type Safety

- Full TypeScript support with inferred types
- Generate types from schema automatically
- Use branded types for IDs and foreign keys
- Leverage Drizzle's type-safe query builder
